                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="42206" author="jlevi" created="Tue, 24 Jul 2012 15:16:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a blocker for 2.4. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41104" author="adilger" created="Mon, 25 Jun 2012 14:55:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, I&apos;d always thought it as being &quot;Distributed NamespacE&quot;, and the wiki page confirms this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s a bit of an internal play on words (letters, really), since the previous implementation of this functionality was called &quot;Clustered MetaData&quot; (CMD), and +1 for each letter gives &quot;DNE&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41103" author="rhenwood" created="Mon, 25 Jun 2012 14:36:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s an easy one for me: Distributed NamEspace&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/PUB/Remote+Directories+Solution+Architecture&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/PUB/Remote+Directories+Solution+Architecture&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="40449" author="joshua" created="Tue, 12 Jun 2012 17:24:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My first question about DNE: What&apos;s DNE?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Dance New England?&lt;br/&gt;
Does Not Exist?&lt;br/&gt;
Do not enter?&lt;br/&gt;
Direction Nationale d&apos;Elevage?&lt;br/&gt;
Do not erase?&lt;br/&gt;
Defining New Elegance?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="40447" author="rhenwood" created="Tue, 12 Jun 2012 17:12:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a ticket to build up our body of knowledge about how DNE changes how Lustre file systems are designed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
